title: Euploea westwoodii
text:
Euploea westwoodii, or Westwood's king crow, is a <a href="butterfly">butterfly</a> in the family <a href="Nymphalidae">Nymphalidae</a>. It was described by <a href="Cajetan%20Felder">Cajetan Felder</a> and <a href="Rudolf%20Felder">Rudolf Felder</a> in 1865. It is found in the <a href="Celebes">Celebes</a> in the <a href="Australasian%20realm">Australasian realm</a>.
Etymology.
The species is named for <a href="John%20Obadiah%20Westwood">John Obadiah Westwood</a>.
